      <abstract displayLabel="Abstract">Intrusion detection systems (IDSs) are software or hardware systems
                that automate the process of monitoring the events occurring in a computer system or
                network, analyzing them for signs of security problems. As network attacks have
                increased in number and severity over the past few years, intrusion detection
                systems have become a necessary addition to the security infrastructure of most
                organizations. This guidance document is intended as a primer in intrusion detection
                , developed for those who need to understand what security goals intrusion detection
                mechanisms serve, how to select and configure intrusion detection systems for their
                specific system and network environments, how to manage the output of intrusion
                detection systems, and how integrate intrusion detection functions with the rest of
                the organizational security infrastructure.</abstract>
